radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is fluid filled and dilated, measuring 1.3 cm, with a hyperenhancing wall. No abscess is seen. There is a moderate amount of intraperitoneal and pelvic free fluid with enhancement of the peritoneum in the right lower quadrant. The stomach and small bowel are decompressed and fluid filled. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys appear normal. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymph node enlargement by CT size criteria. No abdominal wall hernia is seen. The urinary bladder is within normal limits.
